  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Season the roast with salt, pepper, thyme, and rosemary.",
    "Place the roast in a copper-mug or a similar vessel.",
    "Dot the top of the roast with butter.",
    "Roast in the preheated oven for 1 hour.",
    "After 1 hour, reduce the heat to 300°F (150°C) and continue roasting for an additional 2 hours.",
    "Baste the roast with the pan juices every 30 minutes.",
    "Remove the roast from the oven and let it rest for 10 minutes.",
    "Serve the roast with the pan juices spooned over the top.",
    "Squeeze the juice from the unwaxed lime over the top of the roast (about 1 tablespoon)."
